beer.beer_description:
Our 2018 Barleywine was brewed with a blend of New Zealand specialty malts and all-Australian hops.

The wort weighed in at a hefty 24 degrees Plato, making this a job for super Yeast – Whitelabs San Diego Super Yeast, to be specific.

This aggressive strain attenuated the fermenting beer to our desired range, resulting in a strong, balanced beer with a dry finish.

APPEARANCE:
Light chestnut with red highlights.
AROMA:
Toffee and caramelised sugar, mild woody notes and hints of whisky.
FL AVOUR:
Full mouthfeel with a sweet forward palate. Dry finish with some lingering warmth.
